{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_07_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "07 - A Mad Tea-party",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.757,
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 487.008,
  "page_end_sec": 732.5,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 487.008,
      "end": 489.02,
      "text": "\"'I'm afraid I don't know one,' said Alice,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 489.16,
      "end": 490.32,
      "text": "rather alarmed at the proposal."
    },
    {
      "start": 492.096,
      "end": 494.36,
      "text": "\"'Then the Dormouse shall,' they both cried.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 494.62,
      "end": 495.02,
      "text": "\"'Wake up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.04,
      "end": 497.76,
      "text": "Dormouse!' And they pinched it on both sides at once."
    },
    {
      "start": 498.64,
      "end": 501.28,
      "text": "The Dormouse slowly opened his eyes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 501.88,
      "end": 504.14,
      "text": "\"'I wasn't asleep,' he said in a hoarse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 504.2,
      "end": 504.9,
      "text": "feeble voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 505.78,
      "end": 507.94,
      "text": "\"'I heard every word you fellows were saying.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 508.86,
      "end": 509.84,
      "text": "Tell us a story,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 510.02,
      "end": 510.86,
      "text": "said the March Hare."
    },
    {
      "start": 511.28,
      "end": 511.4,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 511.52,
      "end": 512.02,
      "text": "please do,"
    },
    {
      "start": 512.2,
      "end": 512.74,
      "text": "pleaded Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 513.62,
      "end": 514.46,
      "text": "And be quick about it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 514.58,
      "end": 515.32,
      "text": "added the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 515.4,
      "end": 517.48,
      "text": "or you'll be asleep again before it's done."
    },
    {
      "start": 519.232,
      "end": 521.32,
      "text": "Once upon a time there were three little sisters,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 521.66,
      "end": 523.48,
      "text": "the Dormouse began in a great hurry,"
    },
    {
      "start": 524.22,
      "end": 525.54,
      "text": "and their names were Elsie,"
    },
    {
      "start": 525.56,
      "end": 525.84,
      "text": "Lacey,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.02,
      "end": 526.64,
      "text": "and Tilly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.8,
      "end": 528.56,
      "text": "and they lived at the bottom of a well."
    },
    {
      "start": 529.6,
      "end": 530.38,
      "text": "What did they live on,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 530.4,
      "end": 530.88,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 531.06,
      "end": 534.06,
      "text": "who always took a great interest in questions of eating and drinking?"
    },
    {
      "start": 535.89,
      "end": 537.46,
      "text": "They lived on treacle,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 537.7,
      "end": 538.68,
      "text": "said the Dormouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.78,
      "end": 540.16,
      "text": "after thinking a minute or two."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.94,
      "end": 542.44,
      "text": "They couldn't have done that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 542.52,
      "end": 542.82,
      "text": "you know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.0,
      "end": 544.15,
      "text": "Alice gently remarked."
    },
    {
      "start": 544.22,
      "end": 545.14,
      "text": "They'd have been ill."
    },
    {
      "start": 546.4,
      "end": 546.84,
      "text": "So they were,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 547.12,
      "end": 547.9,
      "text": "said the Dormouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 548.0,
      "end": 548.76,
      "text": "very ill."
    },
    {
      "start": 549.3,
      "end": 552.28,
      "text": "Alice tried a little to fancy to herself what"
    },
    {
      "start": 552.38,
      "end": 554.84,
      "text": "such an extraordinary way of living would be like,"
    },
    {
      "start": 554.96,
      "end": 556.72,
      "text": "but it puzzled her too much,"
    },
    {
      "start": 556.86,
      "end": 557.86,
      "text": "so she went on."
    },
    {
      "start": 558.48,
      "end": 560.28,
      "text": "But why did they live at the bottom of a well?"
    },
    {
      "start": 561.44,
      "end": 562.38,
      "text": "Take some more tea,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 562.66,
      "end": 564.65,
      "text": "the March Hare said to Alice very earnestly."
    },
    {
      "start": 565.74,
      "end": 566.64,
      "text": "I've had nothing yet,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 566.78,
      "end": 568.44,
      "text": "Alice replied in an offended tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 568.9,
      "end": 569.86,
      "text": "so I can't take more."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.28,
      "end": 572.72,
      "text": "You mean you can't take less,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 573.04,
      "end": 573.7,
      "text": "said the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 574.4,
      "end": 576.76,
      "text": "It's very easy to take more than nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 578.016,
      "end": 579.42,
      "text": "Nobody asked your opinion,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 579.64,
      "end": 580.12,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 581.504,
      "end": 583.24,
      "text": "Who's making personal remarks now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 583.58,
      "end": 584.98,
      "text": "the Hatter asked triumphantly."
    },
    {
      "start": 586.3,
      "end": 588.5,
      "text": "Alice did not quite know what to say to this,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 588.6,
      "end": 591.44,
      "text": "so she helped herself to some tea and bread and butter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 591.56,
      "end": 594.28,
      "text": "and then turned to the Dormouse and repeated her question,"
    },
    {
      "start": 595.12,
      "end": 596.82,
      "text": "Why did they live at the bottom of a well?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 598.05,
      "end": 601.18,
      "text": "The Dormouse again took a minute or two to think about it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 601.22,
      "end": 602.12,
      "text": "and then said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 602.76,
      "end": 603.84,
      "text": "It was a treacle well."
    },
    {
      "start": 605.184,
      "end": 606.32,
      "text": "There's no such thing,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 606.64,
      "end": 608.32,
      "text": "Alice was beginning very angrily,"
    },
    {
      "start": 608.34,
      "end": 611.18,
      "text": "but the Hatter and the March Hare went shh."
    },
    {
      "start": 612.7,
      "end": 614.9,
      "text": "And the Dormouse sulkily remarked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 615.1,
      "end": 616.52,
      "text": "If you can't be civil,"
    },
    {
      "start": 616.66,
      "end": 618.62,
      "text": "you'd better finish the story for yourself."
    },
    {
      "start": 619.94,
      "end": 620.3,
      "text": "No,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 620.46,
      "end": 621.28,
      "text": "please go on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 621.44,
      "end": 622.68,
      "text": "Alice said very humbly."
    },
    {
      "start": 623.08,
      "end": 624.52,
      "text": "I won't interrupt you again."
    },
    {
      "start": 624.72,
      "end": 626.38,
      "text": "I dare say there may be one."
    },
    {
      "start": 627.26,
      "end": 627.58,
      "text": "One,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 627.58,
      "end": 627.82,
      "text": "indeed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 628.18,
      "end": 629.66,
      "text": "said the Dormouse indignantly."
    },
    {
      "start": 630.0,
      "end": 630.3,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 630.42,
      "end": 631.86,
      "text": "he consented to go on."
    },
    {
      "start": 633.34,
      "end": 634.96,
      "text": "And so these three little sisters,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 635.16,
      "end": 636.56,
      "text": "they were learning to draw,"
    },
    {
      "start": 636.64,
      "end": 636.92,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 637.8,
      "end": 638.44,
      "text": "What did they draw,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 638.6,
      "end": 639.18,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 639.28,
      "end": 640.38,
      "text": "quite forgetting her promise."
    },
    {
      "start": 640.77,
      "end": 641.52,
      "text": "Treacle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 641.66,
      "end": 642.48,
      "text": "said the Dormouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 642.58,
      "end": 644.32,
      "text": "without considering at all this time."
    },
    {
      "start": 645.02,
      "end": 646.6,
      "text": "I want a clean cup,"
    },
    {
      "start": 646.84,
      "end": 647.86,
      "text": "interrupted the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 647.96,
      "end": 649.72,
      "text": "Let's all move one place on."
    },
    {
      "start": 650.32,
      "end": 651.9,
      "text": "He moved as he spoke,"
    },
    {
      "start": 652.1,
      "end": 653.44,
      "text": "and the Dormouse followed him."
    },
    {
      "start": 653.56,
      "end": 655.44,
      "text": "The March Hare moved into the Dormouse's"
    },
    {
      "start": 655.54,
      "end": 655.66,
      "text": "place,"
    },
    {
      "start": 655.84,
      "end": 659.3,
      "text": "and Alice rather unwillingly took the place of the March Hare."
    },
    {
      "start": 660.0,
      "end": 660.88,
      "text": "The Hatter was the"
    },
    {
      "start": 660.98,
      "end": 663.26,
      "text": "only one who got any advantage from the change,"
    },
    {
      "start": 663.46,
      "end": 665.92,
      "text": "and Alice was a good deal worse off than before,"
    },
    {
      "start": 666.3,
      "end": 669.36,
      "text": "as the March Hare had just upset the milk jug into his plate."
    },
    {
      "start": 670.26,
      "end": 672.36,
      "text": "Alice did not wish to offend the Dormouse again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 672.52,
      "end": 674.16,
      "text": "so she began very cautiously,"
    },
    {
      "start": 675.04,
      "end": 676.12,
      "text": "But I don't understand.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 676.58,
      "end": 678.28,
      "text": "Where did they draw the treacle from?"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.62,
      "end": 681.64,
      "text": "You can draw water out of a water well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 681.84,
      "end": 682.4,
      "text": "said the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 682.48,
      "end": 685.3,
      "text": "so I should think you could draw treacle out of a treacle well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 685.52,
      "end": 685.7,
      "text": "eh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 685.82,
      "end": 686.1,
      "text": "stupid?"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.392,
      "end": 688.6,
      "text": "But they were in the well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 688.8,
      "end": 690.08,
      "text": "Alice said to the Dormouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 690.48,
      "end": 692.38,
      "text": "not choosing to notice this last remark."
    },
    {
      "start": 693.78,
      "end": 694.38,
      "text": "Of course they were,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 694.54,
      "end": 695.22,
      "text": "said the Dormouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 695.3,
      "end": 695.72,
      "text": "well in."
    },
    {
      "start": 697.06,
      "end": 700.0,
      "text": "\"'This answer so confused poor Alice that she let the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 700.0,
      "end": 702.72,
      "text": "Dormouse go on for some time without interrupting it."
    },
    {
      "start": 704.2,
      "end": 706.56,
      "text": "\"'They were learning to draw,' the Dormouse went on,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 706.6,
      "end": 708.12,
      "text": "yawning and rubbing its eyes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 708.52,
      "end": 709.86,
      "text": "\"'for it was getting very sleepy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 710.09,
      "end": 712.58,
      "text": "and they drew all manner of things,"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.82,
      "end": 715.2,
      "text": "everything that begins with an M.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 716.416,
      "end": 718.12,
      "text": "\"'Why with an M?' said Alice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 718.976,
      "end": 720.54,
      "text": "\"'Why not?' said the March Hare.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 721.5,
      "end": 722.3,
      "text": "Alice was silent.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 723.08,
      "end": 724.88,
      "text": "The Dormouse had closed its eyes by",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 724.88,
      "end": 727.22,
      "text": "this time and was going off into a doze,"
    },
    {
      "start": 727.5,
      "end": 729.56,
      "text": "but on being pinched by the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 729.96,
      "end": 732.5,
      "text": "it woke up again with a little shriek and went on."
    }
  ]
}